everything you always wanted to know about sleep but were afraid to ask events at stanford everything you always wanted to know about sleep but were afraid to ask facebook twitter email print add to calendar with william c dement md phd stanford university school of medicine professor of psychiatry & behavioral science and chief of the stanford university division of sleep widely regarded as the father of sleep medicine dr dement will review the importance of sleep and the consequences of sleep deprivation three major sleep disorders insomnia narcolepsy and obstructive sleep apnea osa will be discussed in depth including best treatment practices he will also share his personal challenges with insomnia when thursday may 26 2011 7 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where stanford blood center 3373 hillview ave palo alto ca 94304 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags lecture reading health wellness sponsor stanford blood center contact 650 725 2540 kvoneill stanford edu admission free & open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 276 27631 more info last modified may 20 2011
